```text
================================================================================
  TP-LINK ARCHER T2U PLUS - INSTALLATION GUIDE FOR ODROID M1S
================================================================================

  System: Odroid M1S
  OS: Ubuntu 20.04.6 LTS
  Architecture: ARM64
  Adapter: TP-Link Archer T2U Plus AC600 Dual Band
  Chipset: Realtek RTL8821AU

================================================================================
  PREREQUISITES
================================================================================

  - Odroid M1S with Ubuntu 20.04.6 installed
  - Internet connection via Ethernet for initial setup
  - TP-Link Archer T2U Plus USB adapter

================================================================================
  STEP 1: UPDATE SYSTEM AND INSTALL DEPENDENCIES
================================================================================

  Run the following commands:

  sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
  sudo apt install -y build-essential dkms git bc linux-headers-$(uname -r)

================================================================================
  STEP 2: VERIFY USB ADAPTER DETECTION
================================================================================

  Connect the USB adapter and run:

  lsusb | grep -i realtek

  Expected output:
  Bus 001 Device 002: ID 2357:0120 TP-Link Archer T2U PLUS [RTL8821AU]

================================================================================
  STEP 3: DOWNLOAD AND INSTALL DRIVER
================================================================================

  Clone the driver repository:

  git clone https://github.com/morrownr/8821au-20210708.git
  cd 8821au-20210708

  Install the driver:

  sudo ./install-driver.sh

================================================================================
  STEP 4: REBOOT SYSTEM
================================================================================

  sudo reboot

================================================================================
  STEP 5: VERIFY INSTALLATION
================================================================================

  After reboot, verify wireless interface:

  iwconfig

  Expected output:
  wlan0     unassociated  Nickname:"WIFI@RTL8821AU"
            Mode:Managed  Frequency=2.412 GHz  Access Point: Not-Associated
            Sensitivity:0/0
            Retry:off   RTS thr:off   Fragment thr:off
            Power Management:off
            Link Quality:0  Signal level:0  Noise level:0

  Verify interface with ip command:

  ip link show

  Expected output:
  3: wlan0: <NO-CARRIER,BROADCAST,MULTICAST,UP,LOWER_UP> mtu 1500 qdisc mq 
     state DORMANT mode DORMANT group default qlen 1000
     link/ether a8:29:48:af:e9:19 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff

================================================================================
  STEP 6: CONNECT TO WIFI NETWORK
================================================================================

  List available networks:

  nmcli dev wifi list

  Connect to your network:

  nmcli dev wifi connect "YOUR_NETWORK_NAME" password "YOUR_PASSWORD"

  Expected output:
  Device 'wlan0' successfully activated with '802dc69b-a3a9-4de8-9f63-d50de7092fa4'.

  Verify saved connection:

  nmcli connection show

  Expected output:
  NAME                UUID                                  TYPE      DEVICE
  Wired connection 1  aceac0d5-83af-3c9c-8569-de03358d7e99  ethernet  eth0
  YOUR_NETWORK_NAME   802dc69b-a3a9-4de8-9f63-d50de7092fa4  wifi      wlan0

  Test internet connectivity:

  ping -c 4 google.com

================================================================================
  STEP 7: ENABLE WIFI ICON IN GNOME DESKTOP (OPTIONAL)
================================================================================

  If WiFi icon doesn't appear in system tray:

  Install NetworkManager GNOME applet:

  sudo apt install network-manager-gnome

  Run applet:

  nm-applet &

  Configure auto-start:

  mkdir -p ~/.config/autostart

  cat > ~/.config/autostart/nm-applet.desktop << EOF
  [Desktop Entry]
  Type=Application
  Name=Network Manager Applet
  Exec=nm-applet
  Hidden=false
  NoDisplay=false
  X-GNOME-Autostart-enabled=true
  EOF

  Reboot to apply:

  sudo reboot

================================================================================
  FINAL STATUS
================================================================================

  [OK] RTL8821AU Driver installed
  [OK] wlan0 Interface active
  [OK] WiFi Connection established
  [OK] Auto-reconnect configured
  [OK] Desktop icon enabled

================================================================================
  USEFUL COMMANDS
================================================================================

  nmcli dev status                              - Show network device status
  nmcli dev wifi list                           - List available WiFi networks
  nmcli dev wifi connect "SSID" password "PASS" - Connect to WiFi
  nmcli connection show                         - Show saved connections
  nmcli connection delete "SSID"                - Delete saved connection
  iwconfig                                      - Show wireless interface info
  ip addr show wlan0                            - Show IP address
  ping -c 4 google.com                          - Test internet connectivity
  sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager         - Restart NetworkManager

================================================================================
  TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

  PROBLEM: Driver doesn't compile
  SOLUTION: Verify ARM64 platform in Makefile
    cd 8821au-20210708
    nano Makefile
    # Ensure: CONFIG_PLATFORM_ARM64 = y

  PROBLEM: wlan0 interface not appearing
  SOLUTION: Check if module is loaded
    lsmod | grep 8821au
    sudo modprobe 8821au
    dmesg | grep -i rtl

  PROBLEM: Cannot see WiFi networks
  SOLUTION: Bring interface up manually
    sudo ip link set wlan0 up
    sudo iwlist wlan0 scan | grep ESSID

  PROBLEM: NetworkManager not managing WiFi
  SOLUTION: Restart NetworkManager
    systemctl status NetworkManager
    sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager

================================================================================
  NOTES
================================================================================

  - Driver installed via DKMS (auto-recompiles on kernel updates)
  - WiFi connection saved for auto-reconnect on restart
  - Adapter supports 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz bands
  - Tested on Ubuntu 20.04.6 with kernel 4.19.x

================================================================================
  REFERENCES
================================================================================

  Driver Repository: https://github.com/morrownr/8821au-20210708
  Odroid M1S Wiki:   https://wiki.odroid.com/odroid-m1s/odroid-m1s
  TP-Link Product:   https://www.tp-link.com/us/home-networking/usb-adapter/archer-t2u-plus/


================================================================================
